  "response": "The most important question to ask often depends on the context and the situation. However, a universally significant question could be: \"What truly matters to me?\" This question encourages self-reflection, helps clarify values and priorities, and can guide decisions in both personal and professional life. Depending on the setting, other important questions might involve understanding others, such as \"How can I help you?\" or \"What are your thoughts on this?\" These promote connection and understanding.",
